## 📈 PRODUCT METRICS WITH CURSOR

### Key Product Metrics (North Star)

```yaml
1. TTFGE (Time to First Gate Evaluation):
   Definition: Time from signup to first gate status (PASS/FAIL)
   Target: <30 minutes (MTEP <30 min pattern)
   Current: Unknown (need instrumentation)
   Prometheus: product_time_to_first_gate_seconds{user_id, org_id}
   
   Why Critical: Activation metric (70% SaaS churn in first week)

2. Feature Adoption Rate:
   Definition: % of projects using each gate (G0.1-G9)
   Target: >70% (vs industry 30%)
   Current: Unknown (need instrumentation)
   Prometheus: product_gate_usage_total{gate_id, org_id, tier}
   
   Why Critical: Validates problem (60-70% feature waste)

3. User Retention (Cohort Analysis):
   Definition: % users active after 7, 30, 90 days
   Target: 70% (7d), 50% (30d), 40% (90d)
   Current: Unknown (need baseline)
   Prometheus: product_user_retention_rate{cohort, days}
   
   Why Critical: Product-market fit indicator

4. CSAT Score (Post-Gate Evaluation):
   Definition: User satisfaction (1-5 stars) after gate evaluation
   Target: >4.0 average across all gates
   Current: Unknown (need in-app survey)
   Prometheus: product_csat_score{gate_id}
   
   Why Critical: User love indicator (viral growth)

5. Gate Pass Rate:
   Definition: % of gate evaluations that PASS (vs FAIL/PENDING)
   Target: 60-70% (too high = gates too easy, too low = too hard)
   Current: Unknown (need baseline)
   Prometheus: product_gate_pass_rate{gate_id}
   
   Why Critical: Gate difficulty calibration
```

### Cursor Command for Metrics

