## 📚 CPO DECISION EXAMPLES (Historical Reference)

### BFlow Platform Decision

```yaml
Challenge: Scale to 200K SMEs (multi-tenant architecture)

Cursor Analysis:
  Cmd+K: "Show multi-tenant implementation risks"
  Result: tenant_id isolation in all tables, row-level security

CPO Decision: ✅ APPROVED
  Why: Architecture prevents data leakage (highest risk in multi-tenant)
  Validation: No data leakage incidents in 200K users
```

---

### NQH-Bot Recovery Decision

```yaml
Crisis: 78% failure rate (production disaster)

Cursor Investigation:
  Cmd+K: "Find all mocks in codebase"
  Result: 679 mocks found (unit tests, integration tests)

CPO Decision: Zero Mock Policy
  Why: Mocks hide integration failures (contract-first prevents)
  Result: 95% success rate (after OpenAPI 3.0.3 adoption)
```

---

### MTEP Simplification Decision

```yaml
Problem: Platform creation too complex (users give up)

Cursor Prototype:
  Cmd+K: "Design wizard-based onboarding flow"
  Result: 5-step wizard, smart defaults, <30 min target

CPO Decision: ✅ APPROVED
  Why: MTEP <30 min = proven success (user love)
  Result: 90%+ users complete setup (vs 40% before)
```

